==English==

===Etymology===
From the {{LL.}}, from the {{Lat}} ''[[capere]].'' (English usage began around 1688).

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# One who is holding a [[captive]] or captives.
# One who [[catch]]es or has caught or [[capture]]d something or someone.

====Synonyms====
*(''one holding a captive''): [[guard]], [[jailer]], [[kidnapper]]
*(''one who catches someone or something''): [[arrester]], [[nabber]]

